						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Or you could go the Micronics route and drop the whole game to 30 fps; a lot of Game Boy games did this anyway to compensate for the slow-ass LCD on the original model.</div>
<br />
